article.headline: Auburn 78, Tulane 53
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. -- DeWayne Reed scored 20 points to lead Auburn to a 78-53 victory over Tulane on Saturday night. Korvotney Barber added 15 points and 10 rebounds, as the Tigers (10-4) won their seventh consecutive game. Tulane (6-7) jumped out to a 10-0 lead before Frankie Sullivan scored to put Auburn on the board with 16:54 remaining in the first half. Behind its defense, Auburn tied the score at 20-all before outscoring the Green Wave 28-10 in the final 12 minutes of the first half for a 40-27 halftime lead. Led by Auburn native Asim McQueen, Tulane made a run early in the second half, cutting the lead to 48-43. That's when Reed took over, scoring 10 consecutive points as Auburn outscored the Green Wave 30-10 to close the game. McQueen led Tulane with 16 points, Kevin Sims added 14 points and Robinson Luisme had 13 rebounds.
